Package nusri.fyp.demo.state_machine

package nusri.fyp.demo.state_machine
This package contains classes related to the state machine functionality, which manages the flow of the application by processing actions and transitions.
Since:
1.0

  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    AbstractActionObservation
    Abstract class representing a general action-observation entity that can include information such as probability, actions, and objects.
    ActionObservation
    Concrete implementation of action observation, inheriting from AbstractActionObservation.
    Node
    Represents a node in a state machine process.
    SegmentPartitionByDP
    The `SegmentPartitionByDP` class implements a dynamic programming solution to find an optimal partition of data into multiple segments, considering various constraints such as quotas and processing time.
    StateMachine
    StateMachine maintains a state graph based on Node and performs state updates based on different action-object observations.
